Hello everybody.
I am looking to retrieve data from a form that would be in a landing page.
The constraints are that:
I will have to create a form several times and I want to retrieve the data from each form independently.
For the moment I have already created the script which receives the data but I don't know how to send them.
To test my code I am using embed forms for now:
```&lt;script charset="utf-8" type="text/javascript" src="//js-eu1.hsforms.net/forms/embed/v2.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script&gt;
   hbspt.forms.create({
     region: "eu1",
     portalId: "",
     formId: "",
     onFormSubmit: function($form, data) {
       fetch('<http://localhost:3000/HubSpot/form>', {
         method: 'POST',
         headers: {
           'Content-Type': 'application/json',
         },
         body: JSON.stringify(data),
       })
         .then(response =&gt; {
           if (!response.ok) {
             throw new Error('Network response was not ok');
           }
           return response.json();
         })
     }
   });
&lt;/script&gt;```

I am therefore trying to find out how I can send the data from the forms to my server, all methods are good to take :D !!

Thanks in advance
